<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-02T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-02T23:00:00-05:00" n="792" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5144: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                                    Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-03T12:00:00+08:00">May 3,
                                1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 3—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_QT1">Quo Tai-chi</persName>, chief delegate on
                            Chinese side assaulted by Chinese student at his house at about 9:30
                            this morning. Slightly wounded on forehead. It is not believed that his
                            condition is such as to delay proceedings.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_JNT1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>